==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Croton bug
<hw>Cro"ton bug`</hw> <pr>(b⟦ucr⟧g`)</pr>. <ety>[From the
<ets>Croton</ets> water of New York.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small, active, winged species of cockroach (<spn>Ectobia
Germanica</spn>), the water bug. It is common aboard ships, and in
houses in cities, esp. in those with hot-water pipes; -- called also the
<altname>German cockroach</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crotonic</ent>⟦br⟧
